Articles.Content:
I don't think we'd need 3 types so close together in weight. A single version at 5kg should be plenty good. Even if you then require biplanes to run 6 of them, it's only 30kg.

@Qromodynmc, funnily enough, fuel is one of the lightest resources around for this category. Though it's a bit worse for D-25 engine planes as a single radial has about 9 times the fuel consumption as twin sport engine setups. Fueling my 4kg aircraft up to max (90 units, usual combat load of 20-30) would barely add any weight. The gun ammo is much heavier.

**Edited <time datetime="2015-08-09T09:46:25Z" title="08/09/2015 09:46  AM" data-short="8 yr">August 9, 2015</time> by Phearlock**
